7810, 7811, 7812, 7822, 7823 |telephone-area=068 |web=[http://www.ath.be/ www.ath.be] |lat_deg=50 |lat_min=37 |lon_deg=03 |lon_min=46 }} 'Ath' (; ) is a Belgian municipality located in the Walloon province of Hainaut. The Ath municipality includes the old communes of Lanquesaint, Irchonwelz, Ormeignies, Bouvignies, Ostiches, Rebaix, Maffle, Arbre, Houtaing, Ligne, Mainvault, Moulbaix, Villers-Notre-Dame, Villers-Saint-Amand, Ghislenghien (), Isières, Meslin-l'Evêque, and Gibecq. Ath is known as the "City of Giants" after the "Ducasse" festivities which take place every year on the fourth weekend in August. Huge figures representing Goliath, Samson, and other allegoric figures are paraded through the streets, and Goliath's wedding and his famous fight with David are re-enacted.
